I leave for Washington again today; to be a part of that other world, with those other friends. The world of high-drama, high-society, and meaningful fashion. We call ourselves the Gay Mafia, but really all we are colorful sinners under dim-lit passage ways. If that isn't the most fun I've ever known, then I don't know what is. Hehe, I love those guys.

I'm leaving here around 7-something tonight. Ryan, I expect to here word of your big day. ;) Don't leave me hangin'

There was someone I lost a long time ago. He was a man brought to life by his own curiosity and entertained by a good tragedy. This man I knew, he shed many tears; He mourned for those he didn't know but it kept him ever vigilante in his quest to understand the nature of human emotion. The man I knew was hardly a saint. There were cruelties beyond comprehension, committed by his own vocation; he stood without guilt or regret, only remorse but never mercy. He expressed his pleasure and his pain through his hands. With those hands he designed, he created, he engineered genius. The man I knew was never mighty, but neither a vagabond. His intellect, in addition to his stupidity was beyond measure. He was the smartest at times, but always willing to recognize that there was error in his. The man I knew was sane because he realized he was crazy. This man who I once knew died. His name was similar to mine. He spoke it with pride in his voice, mine is spoken with dis-concern. I live to be that man once more, he's now deceased, but he will always live on inside me, forever yearning to break free.

Darling stop confusing me With your wishful thinking Hopeful enbraces Don't you understand? I have to go through this I belong to here where No-one cares and no-one loves No light no air to live in A place called hate The city of fear I play dead It stops the hurting I play dead And hurting stops It's sometimes just like sleeping Curling up inside my private tortures I nestle into pain Hug suffering Caress every ache I play dead It stops the hurting
